{
  "texts": [
    "It is shown that XGDP with GAT achieves the highest PCC and R 2 values, and all XGDP variants and the tCNN model achieve the lowest RMSE.",
    "DeepCDR and TGSA with only expression data obtain the worst RMSE, which is sensible since their research focus lie on incorporation of multi-omics profiles for drug response prediction.",
    "Compared with GraphDRP, our method extends the node features with the circular atomic descriptor as illustrated in Algorithm 1, and introduces multi-head attention to integrate the hidden features of drug and cell line rather than simple concatenation.",
    "It is evident in Table 1 that our refinement in the architecture leads to a better performance, especially on models with GAT convolution.",
    "Compared with tCNN, GAT-and GAT_E-based XGDP outperform tCNN on both PCC and R 2."
  ]
}